dataCells.val: Forrest gets his new leg braces, and walks through Greenbow town with his mother.
Forrest's mother visits the school principal to enroll Forrest. However, the principal takes advantage of Forrest's disability and has sex with Mrs. Gump.

Forrest breaks his leg braces and is able to run as he is being chased by bullies. He runs to Jenny's house where they pray to God after being chased by her abusive father. Jenny's father is arrested and Jenny is moved to her grandmother's house.
Forrest is once more chased by the bullies. However, when he outsmarts and loses them, he runs onto a football field.
Forrest attends the University of Alabama, where he becomes popular in football.
Forrest meets President Kennedy, where he replies to Kennedy's question, How does it feel to be an All-American, I gotta pee.
Forrest graduates from college and enlists in the U.S. Army.
Forrest travels to Vietnam with his fellow platoon-mate Bubba, where they meet Lieutenant Dan Taylor.

After 4/5 months in Vietnam, Forrest's platoon is ambushed by Vietcong soldiers. While most of the platoon retreats, Forrest, Bubba, Dan, Tex and Cleveland stay and fight. The enemies blow up the two soldiers. Forrest eventually runs into the jungle, reaching a riverbank. He runs back to rescue the others. Bubba is shot and dies.
Forrest, Dan, and other soldiers are admitted to the army hospital.
Robert F. Kennedy dies from assassination
Forrest receives the Congressional Medal of Honor, while Lieutenant Dan is discharged and sent back to America. Forrest leaves two weeks later.
Jenny begins a life of drugs and sex, while Forrest plays ping-pong as he teaches veterans as Neil Armstrong lands on the Moon.
Forrest meets Bubba's family to tell them of his deal with Bubba. Later, he visits Bubba's grave to tell him of his journey to China and his money that he will spend on a shrimping boat.
Forrest purchases a shrimping boat and names it Jenny. Meanwhile, in California, Jenny almost commits suicide after taking drugs.
Lt. Dan joins Forrest on his shrimping boat. After several failed attempts, Lt. Dan sarcastically tells Forrest to pray for the shrimp, which he does.
Forrest and Lt. Dan steer through Hurricane Carmen.
Forrest and Lt. Dan catch hundreds of shrimp, obtaining a monopoly in the shrimp industry.
Forrest launches the Bubba Gump Shrimp Corporation with Lt. Dan. They are subsequently featured on hats and magazines.
Mrs. Gump dies of cancer, and Forrest retires from shrimping, leaving his proceeds to Lt. Dan. Meanwhile, the Greenbow City Council gives Forrest a job mowing lawns.
Lt. Dan invests his and Forrest's money in Apple Computers, and the two become wealthy.
Construction on a church funded by Forrest begins.
Jenny leaves Forrest again. On impulse, he goes out for a little run. Eventually, he runs across America four times.
Forrest stops jogging throughout the country for the first time in three years.
Forrest receives a letter from Jenny while watching the news covering Ronald Reagan's attempted assassination.

Forrest Gump sits on a bench, relaying his story to others, including a nurse, a woman with a baby, an overweight man, and an elderly woman. The elderly woman tells Forrest where Jenny's house is. He meets Jenny and her son, Young Forrest, and Jenny tells him that he's his father.
Jenny passes away from her disease.

Forrest visits her grave, and gives her a letter from Little Forrest, where he wonders out loud if dying is a part of life, or if it's in our own destiny. He says goodbye to Jenny, and walks away from the gravestone.
Little Forrest gets on his bus for his first day of school.

Forrest becomes a national ping-pong champion. He travels to China where he plays against some of their ping-pong champions. When he returns, he goes on the Dick Cavett show with John Lennon, and goes to live with Lt. Dan, who is now retired from the Army.
